Codec24Net is a port of Codec2 codec to .NET framework.

Codec2 is an open source low bit rate speech codec, that's developed by David Rowe. More details can be found here.

Currently, the 0.1 aplha version has been ported to .NET 4.0 just to proof the concept. Here you can find next things in sources:

a library with a codec;
a tool to encode/decode pcm files (8Khz, mono, 16 bit);
and a few encoded/decoded sound files.